From: Lin Ma <linma@zju.edu.cn>
Date: Tue, 25 May 2021 14:39:02 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: fix the erroneous flush_work() order
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.12.10
Git-commit: 6a137caec23aeb9e036cdfd8a46dd8a366460e5d

commit 6a137caec23aeb9e036cdfd8a46dd8a366460e5d upstream.

In the cleanup routine for failed initialization of HCI device,
the flush_work(&hdev->rx_work) need to be finished before the
flush_work(&hdev->cmd_work). Otherwise, the hci_rx_work() can
possibly invoke new cmd_work and cause a bug, like double free,
in late processings.

This was assigned CVE-2021-3564.

This patch reorder the flush_work() to fix this bug.

